1. Basic Definitions.

  "Covered Work" means the Received Work or a Derived Work.

  "Derived Work" means a work of authorship that copies from, modifies,
  adapts, is based on, contains, transforms or translates all or part of
  the Received Work such that copyright permission is required. Derived
  Works do not include Mere Aggregation or the mere making of a verbatim
  copy of the Received Work.

  "Distribute" means to transfer or make available a copy to someone else
  (in the case of an organization, to someone outside of the
  organization), such that copyright permission is required.

  "Distributor" means Us and anyone else who Distributes a Covered Work.

  "Mere Aggregation" means an aggregation of a Covered Work with a Separate
  Work. However, if the license of such an aggregation restricts users from 
  exercising rights in the Covered Work given by this License, the 
  aggregation is not Mere Aggregation.

  "Object Code" means any form of a work that is not Source Code.

  "Received Work" means the particular work of authorship We license to you
  under this License.

  "Separate Work" means a work that is separate from and independent of a
  particular Covered Work and is not by its nature an extension or
  enhancement of the Covered Work, and/or a runtime library, standard
  library or similar component bundled with a Separate Work that is used to
  generate an Object Code form of the Covered Work.

  "Source Code" means the preferred form of a work for making modifications
  to it.

  "We"/"Us"/"Our" refers to the individual or organization that places the
  Received Work under this License.

