9. Object Code Distribution.

   "Corresponding Source" of a Covered Work means (i) the Source Code of
   the Covered Work; (ii) all scripts, instructions and information known
   to you necessary for a skilled developer to build, compile, generate 
   and modify the Covered Work; (iii) all relevant interface definition 
   files; (iv) the Source Code of shared libraries that the Covered Work is 
   specifically designed to require, such as by intimate data communication 
   or control flow between those libraries and parts of the Covered Work; 
   and (v) a list clearly identifying all Separate Works that were used in 
   building, compiling, generating and installing the Covered Work. 
   Corresponding Source must be in machine-readable form.

   You may Distribute a Covered Work in Object Code form, provided that:

   a) For Object Code Distributed in a physical product or tangible storage
      medium ("Product"): you accompany the Product with either: (i) a
      durable physical medium customarily used for software interchange
      that contains the Corresponding Source, or (ii) notice of a network 
      location through which the Corresponding Source is available, for the
      Minimum Period, under this License and at no charge. "Minimum Period"
      means the longer of (i) two years from the date of your Distribution 
      of the Covered Work in the Product, or (ii) the period during which 
      you offer spare parts or customer support for the Product.

   b) For Object Code Distributed from a network location: you accompany
      the Object Code with clear directions indicating how the
      Corresponding Source may be obtained under this License from a
      network location at no further charge and in a reasonably equivalent
      manner.

